cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.SY, cs.AI 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) - This paper focuses on analyzing the dynamics of gated recurrent units (GRUs), which are specialized memory elements for building recurrent neural networks. Therefore, cs.NE is the most likely sub-category.
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper discusses the success of GRUs in natural language, speech, and video processing, which are all applications of machine learning. 
3. cs.CL (Computation and Language) - The paper mentions natural language processing as one of the applications of GRUs, which falls under the scope of cs.CL.
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper uses continuous time analysis to gain intuition on the inner workings of GRU networks, which is related to systems and control.
5. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper discusses the success of GRUs in various AI applications, such as natural language processing and video processing.
